  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d91\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0daf\u0db8\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ex-President's overseas expenses are not from government money",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Government Information Department says that the former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa will not spend government money on any of his expenses abroad and all those expenses will be borne by the former President's personal money.",
        "At the press conference held today (16) at the government news department auditorium to announce the decisions of the cabinet of the week, a media person raised a question about the foreign expenses of the former president. Some media had reported that the former and current presidents are legally entitled to certain privileges when the Minister of Mass Media Bandula Gunawardena mentioned that the government is spending money on the foreign expenses of the former president. The minister said that he will look into this further.",
        "Former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa informed that the reports published by some media about his overseas expenses are incorrect and emphasized that all the expenses are spent on his personal money."
      ],
